children.characters:
Instructions
0. Play around with Figma and get used to using the software.
1. Open the My List Page in the Pages section of the Layers Tab.
2. Go to the Assets Tab and go to Local Components > Components > Chararcter Display > Character Display
     and drag it into the frame. Make sure the new Character Display is under List > Group.
3. Change the following by swapping instances (More info at https://help.figma.com/article/306-using-instances#swap):
    a) Character Display > Character/Base > Contents > Card
      - To select the Magical Girls appropriate picture and rank
      - Swap instance: Character Image > Card > [Name] >  Rank [Rank]
    b) Character Display > Character/Base > Contents > Background
      - To select the appropriate background for the Magical Girls attribute
    c) Character Display > Character/Base > Star
      - To select the appropriate stars for the Magical Girls rank
    d) Character Display > Character/Base > Attribute
      - To select the corresponding attribute for the Magical Girl
    e) Character Display > Character/Base > Frame
      - To select the appropriate rank for the Magical Girls rank
    f) Character Display > Magic
      - To select the Magic Level (memorial slots) for the Magical Girl
    g) Character Display > Magia
      - To select the Magia Level for the Magical Girl
      -  Can select the specific Magia Level and the Episode Level (Magia/Level M-E)
    h) Character Display > Level
      - To indicate the Level of the Magical Girl
      - Make sure to select the right side of text box to edit the level (not the Lvl. text)
4. Repeat set 3 for all the Magical Girls you want to create displays for,
     rearranging them into a grid to your liking.
5. Enlarge or shrink the size of the frame My List to fit all your displays.
6. Export the frame by going to the Design Tab with the PNG format and selecting Export List. Then save in your desired location.
